        "title": "Dynamic programming Very large data value",
        "body": "<pre><code>  import java.io.*;\n import java.util.*;\n\n public class Solution {\n\npublic static void main(String[] args) {\n    /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT. Your class should be named Solution. */\n\n    Scanner s= new Scanner(System.in);\n    int t1=s.nextInt();\n    int t2= s.nextInt();\n    int n= s.nextInt();\n    double arr[]= new double[20];\n    for(int i=0;i&lt;20;i++){\n    arr[i]=-1;\n\n    }\n    arr[1]= t1;\n    arr[2]=t2;\n\n    if(arr[n]!=-1){\n        System.out.println((long)arr[n]);\n    }\n\n    else{\n        for(int i=3;i&lt;=n;i++){\n           arr[i]= arr[i-2] + Math.pow(arr[i-1],2);\n        }\n        System.out.println((long)arr[n]);\n    }\n\n\n\n}\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This code is a modified Fibonacci series. I want to calculate the tenth digit in this sequence. But the result is very big I want to ask in which type I should cast the answer ? I have used long but it failed...please suggest any other type ...<\/p>\n",
